; --------- Contents ---------

; Section 1: Ramp Overrides
;
;   1.1 - Orthogonal X1 Ramps
;
;     1.1.a - Type A1 Orthogonal Ramps
;        1.1.a.1 - A1 Outside
;        1.1.a.2 - A1 Dual
;        1.1.a.3 - A1 Inside
;        1.1.a.4 - A1 Outside Wide
;
;     1.1.b - Type B1 Orthogonal Ramps
;        1.1.b.1 - B1 Outside
;        1.1.b.2 - B1 Dual
;        1.1.b.3 - B1 Inside
;
;     1.1.d - Type D1 Orthogonal Ramps
;        1.1.d.1 - D1 Outside
;        1.1.d.2 - D1 Inside
;        1.1.d.3 - D1 Outside Wide
;        1.1.d.4 - D1 Wye
;
;     1.1.e - Type E1 Orthogonal Ramps
;        1.1.e.1 - E1 Outside
;        1.1.e.2 - E1 Inside
;        1.1.e.3 - E1 Wye
;
;   1.2 - Orthogonal X2 Ramps
;
;     1.2.a - Type A2 Orthogonal Ramps
;        1.2.a.1 - A2 Outside
;        1.2.a.2 - A2 Outside Wide
;
;     1.2.b - Type B2 Orthogonal Ramps
;        1.2.a.1 - B2 Outside
;
;     1.2.d - Type D2 Orthogonal Ramps
;        1.2.d.1 - D2 Outside
;        1.2.d.2 - D2 Outside Wide
;
;     1.2.e - Type E2 Orthogonal Ramps
;        1.2.e.1 - E2 Outside
;
;   1.3 - Orthogonal X3 Ramps
;
;     1.3.a - Type A3 Orthogonal Ramps
;        1.3.a.1 - A3 Outside
;
;     1.3.d - Type D3 Orthogonal Ramps
;        1.3.a.1 - D3 Outside
;
;   1.4 - Diagonal X1 Ramps
;
;     1.4.a - Type A1 Diagonal Ramps
;        1.4.a.1 - A1 Outside (Diagonal)
;
;   
; Section 2: Branch Overrides
;
; Section 3: Branch FLEX-HT Overrides
;
; Section 4: Unsorted & Test Code

;----------------------------------------------------------
;--------------- Section 1: Ramp Overrides ----------------
;----------------------------------------------------------

;------------------------------------------------
;---------- 1.1 - Orthogonal X1 Ramps -----------
;------------------------------------------------

;------------ 1.1.a - Type A1 Orthogonal Ramps ------------

;---- Start 1.1.a.1 - Orthogonal Type A1 Outside Ramps ----

; Summary - Type A1 Outside
;
; IID begin = 0x578w[00]
; Base version= RHW-2
; Branch = MIS Orthogonal
; Notes:
;    The RHW-12S version of this ramp has an additional tile
;    located on the bottom of the ramp (tile 04).  This is
;    to improve barrier spacing on the L1-L2 branches.
;
;    Some variants of this ramp must override its L1 RHW-2 
;    version in addition to the base version due to overrides
;    of the base in place for the L1 QuickChange plop.
;
; Diagram:
;
;    ..  ||
;    ..  00
;    01  02
;    03  ||
;    ||  ..
;

;----RHW-2----
;---L0---
;---L1---
;Orth to 00 (Down)
